image.altText: Shenae Ciesiolka tackles Emma Tonegato

items.synopsis: The Maroons prevailed 18-10 in a scrappy, high-intensity contest in Western Sydney to take a 1-0 lead in the two-game series. Follow all the action in our live blog.

title.children: Queensland wins Women's State of Origin Game I

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The Queensland women make it a Maroon double! Queensland wins 18-10! There's a bit of push and shove out there at the moment as well! We're not seeing that on the screen. The players are asking the referee if they can shake hands after that pushing and he says that he's rather they waited a minute to cool down. It was error strewn, gritty and whole-hearted from both sets of players. But it was a win for Queensland, who take an 8-point buffer into Game II as they look to win back the Origin Shield.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Full time! Queensland wins Game I!

children.content: The Queensland women make it a Maroon double!
There's a bit of push and shove out there at the moment as well! We're not seeing that on the screen.
The players are asking the referee if they can shake hands after that pushing and he says that he's rather they waited a minute to cool down.
It was error strewn, gritty and whole-hearted from both sets of players.
But it was a win for Queensland, who take an 8-point buffer into Game II as they look to win back the Origin Shield.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Jaime Chapman dives over in the corner. The Maroons played the ball out but then lost it forward, handing the ball straight back to the Blues with a scrum on the ten. Emma Tonegato broke a tackle after Jesse Southwell took the ball to the line off a scrum and her pass to Chapman was perfect and the Blues go over in the corner. Southwell misses the kick, the Maroons lead is now just 18-10. The host s are coming!
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 51' Blues hit back!

children.content: Jaime Chapman dives over in the corner.
The Maroons played the ball out but then lost it forward, handing the ball straight back to the Blues with a scrum on the ten.
Emma Tonegato broke a tackle after Jesse Southwell took the ball to the line off a scrum and her pass to Chapman was perfect and the Blues go over in the corner.
Southwell misses the kick, the Maroons lead is now just 18-10.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Julia Robinson has a double! Queensland shifted the ball to the right side with quick hands, and Shenae Ciesiolka got to the outside of Olivia Kernick and Robinson was able to dot down. The Maroons lead 18-6 - and every point is vital in this two match series. The kick from Temara hits the post! That's a handful she's missed now. Will it be important?
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 45' Queensland score in the corner!

children.content: Queensland shifted the ball to the right side with quick hands, and Shenae Ciesiolka got to the outside of Olivia Kernick and Robinson was able to dot down.
The Maroons lead 18-6 - and every point is vital in this two match series.
The kick from Temara hits the post! That's a handful she's missed now.
